                "invention-title": [
                    "Combined cooling heating and power system integrating solar energy, hydrogen energy storage and heat energy storage",
                    "一种集成太阳能、氢储能和热储能的冷热电联供系统"
                ]
            },
            "abstract": [
                {
                    "p": "The invention discloses a combined cooling heating and power system integrating solar energy, hydrogen energy storage and heat energy storage, which comprises a solar energy utilization and conversion subsystem, a solar heat storage and utilization subsystem, a residual electricity hydrogen production and energy storage subsystem and a hydrogen energy utilization power generation subsystem, and relates to the field of solar energy, energy storage and combined cooling heating and power. According to the combined cooling, heating and power system, solar energy is adopted as main energy input, heat conduction oil is heated and stored through a solar trough type heat collector, and an absorption refrigerator, a heat exchanger and the like are adopted for cooling/heating according to the load requirement of a user; meanwhile, photovoltaic power generation is supplied to users, and redundant solar power is prepared into hydrogen through a proton exchange membrane electrolytic tank to be stored; when solar energy is insufficient, the solid oxide fuel cell uses hydrogen as fuel to generate electricity, exhaust waste heat in the fuel cell is recycled and stored through the heat exchanger, intermittent and fluctuating solar energy can be effectively stored and utilized, the utilization rate of renewable energy sources is increased, and the requirements of users for cold, heat, electricity and hot water are met."
                },
                {
                    "p": "本发明公开一种集成太阳能、氢储能和热储能的冷热电联供系统，包括太阳能利用转化子系统、太阳能热存储与利用子系统、余电制氢储能子系统以及氢能利用发电子系统，涉及太阳能、储能与冷热电联供领域。该冷热电联供系统采用太阳能作为主要能源输入，通过太阳能槽式集热器加热导热油并进行存储，根据用户负荷需求采用吸收式制冷机、换热器等进行供冷/供热；同时利用光伏发电供给用户，多余太阳能电力通过质子交换膜电解池制成氢气进行存储；太阳能不足时，固体氧化物燃料电池以氢气为燃料进行发电，燃料电池中的排气余热通过换热器进行回收、存储，可有效将间歇、波动太阳能进行存储利用，提高可再生能源利用率，满足用户冷、热、电、热水需求。"
                }
            ]
